      @NotNull @NotNull PreferenceObject getPreferences(String preferenceKey)
      Gets the PreferenceObject for the . Never returns null, instead an empty PreferenceObject will be returned if the preference key has no settings associated with it

    • applyPreferencesForPreferenceKey

      void applyPreferencesForPreferenceKey(String preferenceKey, PreferenceObject preferences)
      This overwrites the existing PreferenceObject, it does not merge the preferences.
      Parameters:
      preferenceKey - the preference key to set the preferences for
      preferences - a PreferenceObject of preferences to set

    • isPersisted

      boolean isPersisted()
      Whether or not this UserPreferences object has had its changes persisted. Returns true even if there have been no changes.

    • flush

      void flush()
      Attempts to save the altered preferences to the DataBase if there are any. If this method fails, isPersisted() will continue to return false.
